Baking made simple with this 7 ingredient Persimmon Tartlet by @functional.foods ! 👩‍🍳​

This tart made with a crunchy cookie crust and simple, seasonal ingredients is sure to impress! ✨​

Ingredients: ​
Crust:​
2 boxes of Simple Mills Toasted Pecan Crunchy Cookies​
1/2 C of melted coconut oil​
​
Filling:​
6 Fuyu persimmons​
1/2 pomegranate​
1 jar of fig jam (or fruit spread of choice)​
Ground nutmeg to taste​
A pinch of sea salt​
​
Instructions:​
PREHEAT oven to 325°F. ​
SPRAY a 9 inch tart/pie pan with cooking spray or lightly brush with melted coconut oil.​
PULSE the cookies in a food processor until they are coarsely ground. Add the melted coconut oil and process until the mixture becomes “doughy sand like.” Collect the dough and press into the prepared pan with your fingers.​
BAKE at 325°F for 15 minutes. Let cool.​
SPREAD a layer of the fig jam over the bottom, about 1/8-inch thick.​
REMOVE the stem and leaves from the persimmons. Cut them in half and into thin slices. Lay cut side down and arrange the persimmon slices clockwise in circles. FINISH with a sprinkle of pomegranate seeds, nutmeg, and sea salt.​
HEAT 2 tablespoons fruit spread with 1 ½ teaspoons water. Use a spatula or pastry brush to apply a thin glaze to the fruit on top.​
BAKE the tart back in the oven for another 4-5 minutes at 325°F. Remove from heat and let cool.​

📸 and recipe: @functional.foods

S’mores belong in more places than just the campfire! ⛺️

Here’s how to make this S’mores Ninja CREAMi 👇

Ingredients:
-1 can coconut milk
-1 can coconut creamer
-1 tablespoon cocoa powder
-Drizzle of honey
-Simple Mills Honey Cinnamon Sweet Thins (for topping and mix-in)
-Marshmallow fluff (for mix-in)

Instructions:
1. Combine the coconut milk, coconut creamer, cocoa powder, and a drizzle of honey in the Ninja Creami pint container. Mix until smooth.
2. Freeze the mixture for 24 hours.
3. After freezing, process the pint using the “Lite Ice Cream” or “Creami” setting
4. Once processed, mix in crushed Honey Cinnamon Sweet Thins and marshmallow fluff
5. Top with more Honey Cinnamon Sweet Thins and ENJOY!

Of all the ways to enjoy cottage cheese, this is our favorite (and will be yours too)! 🍨

This recipe is small but mighty:
- 2 cups of high-fat cottage cheese
- 1 tablespoon of maple syrup
- 1 teaspoon of vanilla extract
- handful of Simple Mills Honey Cinnamon Sweet Thins
- Freeze for a minimum of 6 hours
- Garnish with Sweet Thins & dark chocolate chips
